OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA bright start but cloud will
OL,6,Fquickly bubble up allowing a few
OL,7,Fshowers to develop by lunchtime.
OL,8,FShowers then becoming increasingly
OL,9,Ffrequent and heavier later in the day.
OL,10,FFeeling a little less cool but
OL,11,Ftemperatures still below average.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FA showery evening with some
OL,14,Fheavy and thundery showers possible.
OL,15,FShowers continuing overnight although
OL,16,Fbegin to ease a little towards dawn.
OL,17,FTurning chilly in the countryside but
OL,18,Fmainly frost-free.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
